    "markdown": "---\nformat:\n  html:\n    css: styles.css\n    embed-resources: TRUE\n    code-fold: true\n    page-layout: full\n    fig_caption: yes\n---\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n::: narrow-section\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"grid-container\" style=\"display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); justify-items: center;\">\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">256</div>\n<div id=\"highlight-text\">427</div>\n<div style=\"display: block; &#10;              color: #ff6400; &#10;              font-size: 1.25em; &#10;              font-family: Graphik; &#10;              font-weight: bold; &#10;              text-align: center;\">NA</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Currently Eligible for<br>Parole but in Prison</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">Eligible for Parole in<br>the next 1-5 years</div>\n<div id=\"bold-text\">\n<span class=\"tippy html-widget html-fill-item-overflow-hidden html-fill-item\" height=\"338px\" id=\"htmlwidget-1da0064da1a3dec9f8e6\" width=\"100%\"></span>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-1da0064da1a3dec9f8e6\">{\"x\":{\"opts\":{\"placement\":\"bottom\",\"flip\":true,\"theme\":\"light\",\"content\":\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Not Available<\\/b>: .\"},\"text\":\"<span aria-label=\\\"To compare the degrees of indeterminacy, or unpredictability\\n   of time served, of prison-sentencing systems of different jurisdictions,\\n   we use a qualitative ranking framework based on the Robina Institute's\\n   Prison-release Discretion And Prison Population Size Report.<br><br><b>Not Available<\\/b>: .\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" role=\\\"button\\\">Prison Sentencing<br>System&#9432;<\\/span>\"},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n:::\n\n<br>\n\n\n\n::: panel-tabset \n\n## Parole Eligibility\n\n<center>\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">How is Parole Release Eligibility Determined?</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">Individuals are eligible for parole release when they have served a certain percentage of their sentence based on the felony class, felony count, and whether or not their crime was a crime of violence. If serving a consecutive sentence, the time to parole will be added together to determine a parole eligibility date. As will be discussed further below, individuals who committed crimes after July 1, 1996 must be released when eligible unless they have failed to substantially comply with their individual program directive while incarcerated. Experts within the state estimate that around 80%  of individuals are released at their presumptive date. The parole date is calculated on admission. Inmates may request review of their established parole date. The Board must provide the inmate an opportunity to present their factual and legal arguments in order to determine the true parole date.</div>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">People who are Eligible for Parole</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"bar-chart\">No Data</div>\n<br/>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div id=\"body-section\">\n<div id=\"big-section-title\">Offenses</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"regular-text\">In 2020, drugs offenses constituted the most serious sentenced offense for individuals eligible for parole but still in prison, accounting for 38% (96 people) of the parole-eligible prison population.</div>\n<br/>\n<div id=\"pie-chart\">\n<div id=\"htmlwidget-14a111565924e29eb282\" style=\"width:100%;height:325px;\" class=\"highchart html-widget \"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-14a111565924e29eb282\">{\"x\":{\"hc_opts\":{\